 right or liabilities now existing under repealed sections or parts thereof shall not be affected by the repeal.Act June 25, 1948, ch. 645, § 2162 Stat. 862","Repealed, Transferred, and Omitted SectionsAll former sections of Title 18 were repealed, transferred to other titles, or omitted by said act , except for sections 595, 644, 726–1, 726a, 729, 730, and 732 which were repealed by , , the act revising and codifying Title 28, Judiciary and Judicial Procedure, into positive law.June 25, 1948act June 25, 1948, ch. 64662 Stat. 687"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"part","number":"I","heading":"CRIMES","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/ptI","path":"part-i/index.json"},{"type":"part","number":"II","heading":"CRIMINAL PROCEDURE","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/ptII","path":"part-ii/index.json"},{"type":"part","number":"III","heading":"PRISONS AND PRISONERS","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/ptIII","path":"part-iii/index.json"},{"type":"part","number":"IV","heading":"CORRECTION OF YOUTHFUL OFFENDERS","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/ptIV","path":"part-iv/index.json"},{"type":"part","number":"V","heading":"IMMUNITY OF WITNESSES","identifier":"/us/usc/t18/ptV","path":"part-v/index.json"}]}
